</div> 
<p><strong>Dragon Halberd</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Halberds" href="/Halberds" target="">Halberd</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The Dragon Halberd&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> and it is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a>&nbsp;for those users with high <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a> builds who can use the Dragon Halberd to slash <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enemies" href="/Enemies" target="">Enemies</a> while spinning.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Halberd shaped like a dragon, enwreathed with both ice and lightning.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Alas, the Dragonkin Soldiers never attained immortality, and perished as decrepit, pale imitations of their skyborn kin.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Dragon Halberd in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Dragon Halberd weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragonkin Soldier" href="/Dragonkin+Soldier">Dragonkin Soldier</a> boss in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Siofra River" href="/Siofra+River">Siofra River</a>.&nbsp;This Dragonkin Soldier can be accessed by a portal directly south on the map of the Worshipper's Woods on ruins being led up to by a collapsed pillar with an archer sitting atop. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1548&amp;lat=-173.115625&amp;lng=134.068089&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1548&amp;lat=-173.115625&amp;lng=134.068089&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB">Map link</a>] [<a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/rZlWAogpAXk?t=2440">Video location</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Dragon Halberd Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spinning Slash" href="/Spinning+Slash" target="">Spinning Slash</a></li> 
 <li>Spinning Slash on this weapon functions similarly to the standard version, but has an unstated additional effect of imbuing the weapon with additional lightning damage and frostbite build-up on hit for the next 20 seconds. This version of the skill will be faster than the regular <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ash of War: Spinning Slash" href="/Ash+of+War:+Spinning+Slash">Ash of War: Spinning Slash</a> on all other Halberds.</li> 
 <li>Despite scaling better to STR at +10, a more even spread will result in better AR than leaning more into STR for the same level of stat investment (56 STR / 34 DEX = 647AR vs 70 STR / 20 DEX = 639AR, 55 STR / 55 DEX = 694 AR vs 80 STR / 30 DEX = 690 AR).</li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li>Dragon Halberd can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Deals +10% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#dragon"><img title="Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Dragon</a>-type enemies.</li> 
 <li>Deals +5% damage against&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Special Weaknesses#ancient-dragon" href="/Special+Weaknesses#ancient-dragon"><img title="Ancient Dragon" src="/file/Elden-Ring/ancient-dragon-icon-40px.png" alt="ancient dragon icon 40px" width="20">&nbsp;Ancient Dragon</a>-type enemies</li> 
 <li>Spinning Slash buffs this weapon with Ice Lightning, adding 130 Lightning Damage and 80 Frost build up for 20 seconds, much like the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragonscale Blade" href="/Dragonscale+Blade" target="">Dragonscale Blade</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
